=\"row\" | ''[[Samurai Shodown (2019 video game)|Samurai Shodown]]'' #\n| [[Fighting game|Fighting]]\n| [[SNK]]\n| [[Athlon Games]]\n| {{dts|November 19, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|June 25, 2019|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Serious Sam|Serious Sam Collection]]'' #\n| [[First-person shooter|Shooter]]\n| [[Croteam]]\n| [[Devolver Digital]]\n| {{dts|March 3, 2020|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|March 3, 2020|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Shadow of the Tomb Raider]]''\n| [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| [[Eidos Montr\u00e9al]]\n| [[Square Enix]]\n| {{dts|November 19, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|September 14, 2018|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Spitlings'' #\n| [[Arcade game|Arcade]]\n| Massive Miniteam\n| [[HandyGames]]\n| {{dts|February 25 2020|fornmat=mdy}}\n| {{dts|February 25 2020|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Stacks On Stacks (On Stacks)'' #\n| [[Puzzle]]\n| Herringbone Games\n| Herringbone Games\n| {{dts|2020|04|01}}\n| {{dts|2020|04|01}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[SteamWorld Dig]]''\n|[[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Image & Form]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Image & Form]]\n| {{dts|2020|03|10}}\n| {{dts|2013|08|07}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[SteamWorld Dig 2]]'' #\n|[[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| {{dts|2020|03|01}}\n| {{dts|2017|09|21}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[SteamWorld Heist]]''\n|[[Turn-based strategy]]\n| {{dts|2020|03|10}}\n| {{dts|2015|12|10}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[SteamWorld Quest]]'' #\n| [[Role-playing video game|Role-playing]]\n| [[Thunderful Publishing]]\n| {{dts|2020|03|01}}\n| {{dts|2019|04|25}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Superhot]]''\n| [[First-person shooter]]\n| Superhot Team\n| Superhot Team\n| {{dts|2020|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|February 26, 2016|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Thumper (video game)|Thumper]]'' #\n| [[Rhythm game|Rhythm]]\n| Drool\n| Drool\n| {{dts|November 19, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|October 10, 2016|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Tom Clancy's The Division 2]]''\n| [[Third-person shooter]]\n| [[Massive Entertainment]]\n| [[Ubisoft]]\n| {{dts|March 17, 2020|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|March 15, 2019|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Tom Clancy's Ghost Recon Breakpoint]]''\n| [[Tactical shooter]]\n| [[Ubisoft Paris]]\n| [[Ubisoft]]\n| {{dts|December 18, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|October 4, 2019|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Tomb Raider (2013 video game)|Tomb Raider: Definitive Edition]]'' #\n| [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| [[Crystal Dynamics]]\n| [[Square Enix]]\n| {{dts|November 19, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|January 14, 2014|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Trials Rising]]''\n| [[Racing game|Racing]]\n| [[RedLynx]], [[Ubisoft Kiev]]\n| [[Ubisoft]]\n| {{dts|November 19, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|February 26, 2019|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[The Turing Test (video game)|The Turing Test]]''\n| [[Puzzle game|Puzzle]]\n| Bulkhead Interactive\n| Bulkhead Interactive\n| {{dts|2020|format=y}}\n| {{dts|August 30 2016|format=mdy}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Untitled [[Q-Games]] game<ref name=\"forbes-1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/davidthier/2019/03/20/all-3-games-confirmed-for-google-stadia/#595209e37ebe|title=All 3 Games Confirmed For Google Stadia|last=Thier|first=David|date=20 March 2019|website=[[Forbes]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321043952/https://www.forbes.com/sites/davidthier/2019/03/20/all-3-games-confirmed-for-google-stadia/|archivedate=21 March 2019|url-status=live|accessdate=21 March 2019|quote=Assassin's Creed Odyssey was the test case for Project Stream, and people have already played a remote version of this game in a web browser. [...] Google confirmed that Dylan Cuthbert's Q-Games would be building a game around the \"state share\" feature that will allow you to instantly start playing a game at the same moment as a Youtube video or a live Youtube stream. [...] it's hired AAA gaming industry very Jade Raymond to head up a studio called Stadia Games and Entertainment.}}</ref>\n| {{Unknown}}\n| [[Q-Games]]\n| {{Unknown}}\n| {{TBA}}\n| {{TBA}}<!--{{dts|XXXX-XX-XX|format=mdy}}-->\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Watch Dogs: Legion]]''<ref>{{cite tweet | last = Harrison | first = Phil | user = MrPhilHarrison | number = 1138181114600644610 | date = 10 June 2019 | title = Watchdogs Legion coming to #Stadia thanks to @Ubisoft in March 2020.}}</ref>\n| [[Action-adventure game|Action-adventure]]\n| [[Ubisoft Toronto]]\n| [[Ubisoft]]\n| {{tba}}\n| {{tba}}\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[West of Loathing]]''\n| [[Adventure]], [[Role-playing video game|Role-playing]]\n| [[Asymmetric Productions]]\n| [[Asymmetric Productions]]\n| {{dts|2020|}}\n| {{dts|August 10, 2017|}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Windjammers 2]]''\n| [[Sports game|Sports]]\n| [[DotEmu]]\n| [[DotEmu]]\n| {{TBA}}\n| {{TBA}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Wolfenstein: Youngblood]]''<ref name=\"Stadia\" />\n| [[First-person shooter]]\n| [[MachineGames]], [[Arkane Studios]]\n| [[Bethesda Softworks]]\n| {{dts|November 19, 2019|format=mdy}}\n| {{dts|July 26, 2019|format=mdy}}\n|-\n|}\n{{Legend|| outline = #FFFFFF|size=50%|{{Dagger}} ''Exclusive game for Stadia.'' }}\n{{Legend|| outline = #FFFFFF|size=50%|{{Hash}} ''Free with paid subscription \"Stadia Pro\" currently or was in the past.'' }}\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Pre-release ===\nDuring its beta, the service received generally positive initial impressions from reviewers, who felt it met and in some instances, exceeded expectations{{r|Ars T preview|Polygon preview|Verge preview}} and could make game streaming appear as a potentially viable alternative to PC gaming;{{r|Polygon preview|Verge preview}} however, some minor discrepancies and technical issues were nonetheless noted.\n\nReviewers reported that the streaming service had low latency and felt as if the game was being played locally.{{r|Polygon preview|Verge preview}} Despite this, depending on Wi-Fi speeds, the game sometimes compressed its [[screen resolution]] or lagged.{{r|Verge preview}} A test by ''[[The Verge]]'' found no lag issues over a wired ethernet connection, and occasional stuttering on a shared Wi-Fi connection.{{r|Verge preview}} However, even on a wired connection, the stream did not output at 4K resolution and occasionally went fuzzy with [[compression artifact]]ing. The reviewer reported the best experience on Google's [[Chromebook Pixel]].{{r|Verge preview}} ''[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]'' found the service's audio compression noticeable.{{r|Polygon preview}} ''[[Ars Technica]]'' remarked that Project Stream's login sequence was far simpler than that of other services.{{r|Ars T preview}} [[Eurogamer|Digital Foundry]] performed a hands-on with ''[[Assassin's Creed Odyssey]]'' on a [[Google Pixelbook|Pixelbook]] on the service in Beta, and found that on the testing environment, latency seemed acceptable, but there was a noticeable visual hit. They also remarked that ''Assassin's Creed Odyssey'' was not the best example for testing, as it was already a natively laggy game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/digitalfoundry-2019-hands-on-with-google-stream-gdc-2019|title=Google Stadia hands-on: streaming analysis and controller impressions|publisher=[[Eurogamer]]|date=2019-03-19|quote=Assassin's Creed Odyssey is perhaps not the best example for testing, as it's natively a fairly laggy game, so it will be interesting to test faster 60fps titles (...) Stadia is perfectly playable and presentable here, but it's clear that there is a noticeable visual hit when the encoder is presented with more a more detail-rich, fast-moving scene process.|accessdate=2019-03-24}}</ref>{{Efn|''Assassin's Creed Odyssey'' was originally designed for gameplay at 30 frames per second.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2019/04/23/assassins-creed-odyssey-pc-graphics-performance-how-to-get-the-best-settings-2/|title=Assassin's Creed Odyssey PC graphics performance: How to get the best settings|author=Katharine Castle|website=Rock Paper Shotgun|date=2018-04-23|accessdate=2019-12-10}}</ref>}}\n\n=== Post-release ===\nStadia received mixed reviews upon its release: [[Metacritic]] lists 0 extremely positive reviews, 8 positive reviews, 29 mixed reviews and 14 negative reviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/feature/google-stadia-cloud-gaming-service-review/ |title=Cloud Gaming Service Review: Google Stadia |last=Dietz |first=Jason |date=18 November 2019 |website=[[Metacritic]] |access-date=9 December 2019}}</ref> ''[[Wired (magazine)|Wired Magazine]]'' described the image quality as \"drab\", but admitted to preferring to play ''Destiny 2'' on a Chromebook instead of a larger gaming laptop.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/review/google-stadia/|title=Stadia Might Be One of Google's Best Products\u2014Eventually|website=WIRED}}</ref> [[VentureBeat]] criticized the service's pricing model, comparing it unfavorably to subscription services such as [[Xbox Game Pass]] and claiming that Stadia \"doesn't matter\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2019/11/18/google-stadia-review-it-works-but-so-what/|title=Google Stadia review \u2014 It works, but it doesn\u2019t matter|date=November 18, 2019}}</ref> ''Digital Foundry'' found that the service was incapable of playing games at 4K resolutions: ''Red Dead Redemption 2'' was found to only run at 1440p, and ''Destiny 2'' ran at only 1080p (albeit at a frame rate higher than that of the console versions).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/digitalfoundry-2019-stadia-tech-review|title=Stadia tech review: the best game streaming yet, but far from ready|first=Richard|last=Leadbetter|date=November 18, 2019}}</ref> Digital Foundry also discovered that games like ''Red Dead Redemption 2'' also struggled to maintain a consistent 60 frames per second, claiming that their test of the game on Chromecast only outputted a solid 30 FPS, while a test on the Chrome browser was an unstable 60 FPS that dropped frequently.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/digitalfoundry/status/1196551514896162816?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1196551514896162816&ref_url=https://mspoweruser.com/google-stadia-red-dead-redemption-2-doesnt-run-at-a-stable-60fps/|title=Interesting to see Stadia RDR2 capture out there running at an unstable 60fps. A bit tired here and Stadia barely runs on my home connection right now for some reason, but Saturday night's Chromecast captures are indeed 30fps, while Chrome browser output seem to be aiming for 60.pic.twitter.com/4p7SXk7JPW|first=Digital|last=Foundry|date=November 18, 2019}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave Stadia three stars out of five, praising the service's technical performance, while criticising its game selection for being too old and only featuring one exclusive.<ref name=\"Guardian Review\">{{cite web |last1=Hern |first1=Alex |title=Google Stadia review \u2013 the console vanishes from video gaming |url=https://www.theguardian.com/games/2019/nov/18/google-stadia-review-gylt |website=The Guardian |accessdate=20 November 2019 |ref=guardian-review |date=18 November 2019}}</ref> ''[[Ars Technica]]'' concluded: \"Early adopters feel like they're getting a beta product here. Wait until next year to see if Google can work out the kinks and prove the service's longevity.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2019/11/google-stadia-might-be-gamings-future-but-in-the-present-it-looks-rough/ |title=Google Stadia launch review: Gaming\u2019s \"future\" looks rough in the present |last=Orland |first=Kyle |date=November 18, 2019 |website=[[Ars Technica]] |access-date=November 21, 2019}}</ref> ''[[S&P Global|S&P Global Market Intelligence]]'' reported that: \"Stadia met with tepid enthusiasm from analysts and early adopters who criticized the service's slate of launch titles and lack of promoted features\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.spglobal.com/marketintelligence/en/news-insights/latest-news-headlines/55612856 |title=Google's new Stadia platform faces muted reception tied to game launch slate  |last=Halder |first=Anser |date=21 November 2019 |website=S&P Global Market Intelligence |access-date=9 December 2019}}</ref> Dieter Bohn from [[The Verge]] has stated that \"I have put in enough hours in enough conditions to say that this is a beta product, and Google should have labeled it as such and launched it differently. Because even in the best conditions, this ain\u2019t the best.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/12/18/21025576/google-stadia-editorial-assassins-creed-beta-game-library|title=Google Stadia should have stayed in beta|website=www.theverge.com}}</ref>\n\nTowards the end of January 2020, Stadia users expressed concern about Google's non-communicative stance on Stadia, outside of its monthly free game additions; these users were concerned about planned features that were to be available in the next few months from Google's initial timeline but yet have been discussed further, such as 4K streaming resolution support. A Google community manager had been following these discussions and expressed sympathy that users have been waiting for information, and stated that there is news that they could not yet discuss but will be able to soon.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/357269/Stadia_owners_on_Reddit_are_blasting_Google_over_radio_silence_and_lack_of_support.php | title = Stadia owners on Reddit are blasting Google over radio silence and lack of support | first=  Chris | last = Kerr | date = January 28, 2020 | accessdate = January 28, 2020 | work = [[Gamasutra]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/pkeagn/its-increasingly-clear-stadias-launch-was-an-expensive-beta-test | title = It\u2019s Increasingly Clear Stadia\u2019s Launch Was an Expensive Beta Test | first=  Patrick | last=  Kelpek | date = January 28, 2020 | accessdate = January 28, 2020 | work = [[Vice (website)|Vice]] }}</ref> Google responded by pointing users to its Stadia community site where it was providing weekly updates on the progress on Stadia's features, and that in terms of future games, they mostly had left it to publishers to announce when these games would be available on Stadia.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2020-01-30-google-responds-to-complaints-of-slow-stadia-announcements | title = Google responds to complaints of slow Stadia announcements | first = James | last = Batchlor | date = January 30, 2020 | accessdate = January 30, 2020 | work = [[GamesIndustry.biz]] }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n'''Notes'''\n{{Notelist}}\n\n'''Citations'''\n{{reflist|refs=\n[http://androidexide.com/latest-news/google-stadia-game-streaming-service-by-google/ Google Stadia: game streaming service by Google]\n\n<ref name=\"Ars T announce\">{{Cite web |last1=Amadeo |first1=Ron |title=Google announces 'Project Stream'\u2014a 'test' of game streaming in Chrome |work=[[Ars Technica]] |date=2018-10-01 |url=https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2018/10/google-announces-project-stream-a-test-of-game-streaming-in-chrome/ |accessdate=2019-01-01 |df=mdy-all |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225085527/https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2018/10/google-announces-project-stream-a-test-of-game-streaming-in-chrome/ |archive-date=December 25, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Ars T preview\">{{Cite web |last1=Machkovech |first1=Sam |title=Google\u2019s Project Stream: That\u2019s really a full Assassin\u2019s Creed in my browser |work=[[Ars Technica]] |date=2018-10-09 |url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2018/10/googles-project-stream-thats-really-a-full-assassins-creed-in-my-browser/ |accessdate=2019-01-01 |df=mdy-all |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011194804/https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2018/10/googles-project-stream-thats-really-a-full-assassins-creed-in-my-browser/ |archive-date=October 11, 2