ocken, PA |publisher=Combined Books |isbn=978-0-938289-29-6 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/waterloocampaign0000nofi }}\n* {{citation |last1=Oman |first1=Charles |last2=Hall |first2=John A. |year=1902 |title=A History of the Peninsular War |publisher=Clarendon Press |page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=q6pBAQAAMAAJ 119]}}\n* {{Citation |last=Palmer |first=R.R. |year=1956 |title=A History of the Modern World |publisher= New York: Knopf}}\n* {{citation |last=Parkinson |first=Roger |year=2000 |title=Hussar General: The Life of Bl\u00fccher, Man of Waterloo |publisher=Wordsworth Military Library |isbn=978-1840222531 |pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=x58TZVEU_Q4C&lpg=PP1&pg=PA240 240]\u2013241}}\n* {{Citation |last=Parry |first=D.H. |year=1900 |chapterurl=http://gaslight.mtroyal.ab.ca/waterloo.htm |chapter=Waterloo |title=Battle of the nineteenth century |volume=1 |publisher=London: Cassell and Company |accessdate=14 September 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081216071449/http://gaslight.mtroyal.ab.ca/waterloo.htm |archivedate=16 December 2008 |df=dmy-all }}\n* {{citation |last=Paton |first=Callum |date=5 April 2015 |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sciencetech/article-3026442/200-year-old-skeleton-hunchback-soldier-killed-battle-Waterloo-Belgian-car-park-believed-trained-Sussex.html |title=Skeleton of soldier killed at Waterloo discovered under a car park like Richard III |newspaper=Daily Mail Online}}\n* {{Citation |last=Pawly |first=Ronald |title=Wellington's Belgian Allies |series=Men at Arms nr 98. 1815 |publisher=Osprey |year=2001 |pages=37\u201343 |isbn=978-1-84176-158-9}}\n* {{Citation |last=Paxton |first=Robert O. |year=1985 |title=Europe in the 20th Century |publisher= Orlando: Harcourt Brace Jovanovich}}\n* {{Citation |last=Peel |first=Hugues Van |date=11 December 2012 |title=Le soldat retrouv\u00e9 sur le site de Waterloo serait Hanovrien |publisher=[[RTBF]] |url=http://www.rtbf.be/info/regions/detail_le-soldat-retrouve-sur-le-site-de-waterloo-etait-prussien?id=7890492 |language=French}}\n* {{Citation |last=Rapport |first=Mike |date=13 May 2015 |title=Waterloo |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/17/books/review/waterloo.html}}\n* {{Citation |last=Roberts |first=Andrew |year=2001 |title=Napoleon and Wellington| publisher=London: Phoenix Press| isbn=978-1-84212-480-2}}\n* {{Citation |last=Roberts |first=Andrew |year=2005 |title=Waterloo: 18 June 1815, the Battle for Modern Europe |publisher=New York: HarperCollins |isbn=978-0-06-008866-8 |url=https://archive.org/details/waterloojune181800robe }}\n* {{Citation |editor-last=Shapiro |editor-first=Fred R. |year=2006 |title=The Yale Book of Quotations |edition=illustrated |publisher=Yale University Press |isbn=978-0-300-10798-2 |page=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780300107982/page/128 &#91;https://books.google.com/books?id=w5-GR-qtgXsC&pg=PA128 128&#93;] |url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9780300107982/page/128 }}\n* {{Citation |last=Siborne |first=Herbert Taylor |authorlink=H. T. Siborne |year=1891 |title=The Waterloo Letters |location=London |publisher=Cassell & Co. |url=https://archive.org/details/waterlooletterss00sibo}}\n* {{Citation |last=Siborne |first=William |year=1895 |title=The Waterloo Campaign, 1815 |edition=4th |location=Westminster |publisher=A. Constable |url=https://archive.org/stream/waterloocampaig01sibogoog#page/n6/mode/2up}}\n* {{Citation |last=Simms|first=Brendan |year=2014 |title=The Longest Afternoon: The 400 Men Who Decided the Battle of Waterloo |publisher=Allen Lane |isbn=978-0-241-00460-9}}\n* {{Citation |last=Smith |first=Digby |year=1998 |title=The Greenhill Napoleonic Wars Data Book |publisher=London & Pennsylvania: Greenhill Books & Stackpole Books |isbn=978-1-85367-276-7}}\n* {{citation |last=Steele |first=Charles |year=2014 |title=Germany at War: 400 Years of Military History |editor-last=Zabecki |editor-first=David T. |publisher=ABC-CLIO 